latestIgtvVideos.title: My skin routine
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Treating acne doesn’t just involve trying product after product. It encompasses careful cleansing and some simple lifestyle changes. PLEASE DON’T BUY THESE PRODUCTS BLINDLY 

Make up remover :- Bioderma micellar water  A solution to cleanse and soothe sensitive skin from face and eyes. Removes impurities & cleanses the skin.

Exfoliate :- Bioderma white objective moussant is an exfoliating foaming cream that biologically corrects and prevents hyperpigmentation, suitable for face and body.

Face cleanser :-A-derma soothing foaming gel
a soap-free formulation makes cleansing a gentle

Toner :- Avene thermal spray 
Reduces skin sensitivity and helps restore skin balance 

Cream :- Ducray Keracnyl PP Cream is an anti-blemishes care which helps reduce the painful and red spots. 

Sunscreen :- Heliocare's 360 Gel Oil-Free SPF 50 Ideal for acne-prone and sensitive skin 

Acne spot treatment :- Nilac A Gel medicine that helps treat acne by reducing the production of sebum that causes acne.

latestIgtvVideos.title: My acne story
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Finally posted about my skin care , many think i am flawless , girls i am NOT FLAWLESS .i have pore , acne ,acne spots, white heads and pigmentation and its normal to have all these things . Please love yourself with everything you have . just a list below of dont's , things i learnt the hard way :- 

- Don’t do makeup wipes 
- If you wear makeup think about double cleanse 
- No products with fragrance 
- Diy skincare is a big NO NO 
- Sunscreen!!! Every. Single. Day 
- (Drying) Alcohol in ingredients stay away 
- Get a blood test to check if you have any deficiency
- Check if your hormones are balanced ?
- Don't blindly follow everything you see online
